### SECTION 1: CONTENT & COPY (Prompts 1–5)

**Prompt 1 — Social Post from a Core Idea**

> You are an expert social media strategist for service-based businesses. Write a LinkedIn post based on the following idea: [YOUR IDEA]. My audience is [DESCRIBE AUDIENCE]. Write in a direct, conversational tone — no corporate fluff, no generic motivational language. Keep it under 200 words. End with a question that invites real responses.

**Prompt 2 — Email to Your List**

> You are an email copywriter for coaches and consultants. Write an email to my list about [TOPIC]. My audience is [DESCRIBE AUDIENCE]. The goal of this email is [INFORM / SELL / INVITE / NURTURE]. Tone: direct, no filler. Subject line options: give me three variations. Length: 200–300 words max.

**Prompt 3 — Turn a Rambling Idea into a Clean Post**

> I have a rough idea I want to turn into a clean social media post. Here's my raw thinking: [PASTE YOUR UNEDITED THOUGHTS]. Clean this up, sharpen the message, and write it as a post for [PLATFORM]. Keep my voice — don't add corporate language or generic phrases. Give me two versions: one punchy and short (under 100 words), one with more depth (200 words).

**Prompt 4 — Blog Post Outline**

> You are a content strategist for service-based businesses. Create a detailed blog post outline for the topic: [TOPIC]. My target reader is [DESCRIBE READER]. The post should position me as an expert, provide genuine value, and end with a clear CTA to [YOUR OFFER / SERVICE / OPT-IN]. Include: working headline, 5–7 section headers with 2–3 bullet points each, intro angle, and closing CTA direction.

**Prompt 5 — Repurpose One Piece of Content into 5 Formats**

> Here is a piece of content I've already created: [PASTE CONTENT]. Repurpose this into five different formats: (1) a LinkedIn post, (2) a short-form video script (60–90 seconds), (3) an email to my list, (4) a Twitter/X thread (5–7 tweets), (5) a story post for Instagram or Facebook. Keep the core message consistent. Match the tone of the original.

